               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1043" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1043" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1043" type="surname" value="POCOCK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1043" type="given" value="EMMA"></interp>EMMA POCOCK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am nine years old, and live with my father, James Pocock, in Chapel-street, Curtain-road. On Wednesday night, the 9th of February, I was at the top of Phipps-street, near the Curtain-road, with an accordion in my hand, playing it—the prisoner came up, and said, "Let me have a play?"—I said, "No, you will run away with it"—he snatched it out of my hand, and ran away—I called out, "Stop thief—he ran down Johnson's-place, which is no thoroughfare—Mr. Bradford ran after him, and took the accordion from him—this now produced is it—it belongs to my father.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1044" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1044" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1044" type="surname" value="BRADFORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1044" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE BRADFORD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a postman. On Wednesday, the 9th of February, I heard a cry of "Stop thief," and saw the prisoner running—he took a turning which is no thoroughfare—I took hold of him—he said, "For God's sake, let me go"—I took this accordion from him, and gave it to the policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1045" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1045" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1045" type="surname" value="STRUTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1045" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN STRUTT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 219.) The prisoner was given to me—he said he only did it for play—I asked why he ran away—he said, because the people were running after him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I took it have a play—I took it to the lamp to look at it, and she cried "Stop thief."</p>
